### Component(s)

metricshub-agent

### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.

The MetricsHub Agent exposes a REST API (`/api/**`, `/auth/**`) but has no machine-readable API specification or interactive documentation. We should integrate springdoc-openapi to auto-generate an OpenAPI 3.x spec and serve Swagger UI alongside the existing React SPA without conflicts.

### Solution details

## Motivation

- Developers and integrators need a reliable, always-up-to-date API reference.
- Swagger UI provides an interactive way to explore and test endpoints during development.
- An OpenAPI spec enables client SDK generation and automated API testing.

## Scope

### 1. Add the `springdoc-openapi` dependency

Add to pom.xml:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springdoc</groupId>
    <artifactId>springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui</artifactId>
    <version>compatible-version</version>
</dependency>
```

This provides:
- OpenAPI spec endpoint at `/v3/api-docs`
- Swagger UI at `/swagger-ui/index.html`

### 2. Create an `OpenApiConfig` configuration class

In `org.metricshub.web.config`, create a `@Configuration` bean that defines global API metadata (`Info`, License, etc.).

### 3. Annotate all REST controllers

Add OpenAPI annotations to every controller in `org.metricshub.web.controller`:

| Controller | `@Tag` name |
|---|---|
| `AgentController` | Agent |
| `AuthenticationController` | Authentication |
| `ChatController` | Chat |
| `ConfigurationFilesController` | Configuration Files |
| `ExplorerController` | Explorer |
| `LogFilesController` | Log Files |
| `OtelCollectorController` | OTel Collector |
| `OtelConfigurationFilesController` | OTel Configuration Files |
| `UserController` | User |

For each endpoint method, add `@Operation` (summary + description) and `@ApiResponse` annotations. For request/response DTOs, add `@Schema` annotations.

### 4. Prevent conflict with the React SPA â€” critical

The current `UiConfig.addResourceHandlers()` uses a catch-all `/**` resource handler with a `PathResourceResolver` that falls back to `index.html` for any unresolved path (SPA routing). This **will intercept Swagger UI requests** and return the React app instead.

**Fix:** In `UiConfig.java`, modify the `PathResourceResolver.getResource()` override to return `null` for springdoc paths, allowing Spring MVC to dispatch them to springdoc's built-in controllers:

```java
@Override
protected Resource getResource(String resourcePath, Resource location) throws IOException {
    // Let springdoc handle its own paths
    if (resourcePath.startsWith("v3/api-docs") || resourcePath.startsWith("swagger-ui")) {
        return null;
    }

    Resource requested = location.createRelative(resourcePath);
    if (requested.exists() && requested.isReadable()) {
        return requested;
    }

    // SPA fallback
    return location.createRelative("index.html");
}
```

### 5. Security â€” no changes needed

The existing `SecurityConfig` already scopes authentication to `/api/**`, `/sse`, and `/mcp/message` (Order 1). The `defaultFilterChain` (Order 2) permits all other requests. Since `/swagger-ui/**` and `/v3/api-docs/**` don't match the first chain, they will be publicly accessible out of the box.

If Swagger UI should later be restricted, those paths can be added to the authenticated filter chain with explicit `permitAll()` or `authenticated()` rules.

## Files impacted

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| pom.xml | New dependency |
| `o.m.web.config.OpenApiConfig` (new) | Global OpenAPI metadata bean |
| `o.m.web.config.UiConfig` | Exclude swagger paths from SPA fallback |
| `o.m.web.controller.*Controller` | `@Tag`, `@Operation`, `@ApiResponse` annotations |
| `o.m.web.dto.*` | `@Schema` annotations on key DTOs |



